cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper discusses fairness in network resource allocation, which is a topic commonly studied in the computer networking community. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses algorithms and simulations, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of switch algorithms and convergence analysis suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
